<p>
  It strives to conform to level <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">AA compliance for the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (<abbr>WCAG</abbr>) 2.2</a>. These are guidelines that explain how to make web content easier to use for disabled people.
</p>
<p>
  The code powering this site is <a href="https://www.w3.org/standards/">standards-compliant <abbr>HTML</abbr>, <abbr>CSS</abbr>, and JavaScript</a>. Any person using a past, present, or future browser that honors these standards should be capable of navigating this site.
</p>
<p>
  In addition to being tested on <a href="{{ '/colophon#browser-list' | url }}">modern browsers</a>, this site has been checked for screen reader ease of use using <a href="http://www.apple.com/accessibility/osx/voiceover/">Voice&#8202;Over</a>, <a href="http://www.nvaccess.org/"><abbr>NVDA</abbr></a>, and <a href="https://www.freedomscientific.com/Products/Blindness/JAWS"><abbr>JAWS</abbr></a>. It is also audited using <a href="http://wave.webaim.org/about"><abbr>WAVE</a>, and <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/axe/lhdoppojpmngadmnindnejefpokejbdd"><abbr >axe</abbr></a>, and <a href="https://tenon.io/">Tenon</a> automated accessibility testing services.
</p>
<p id="accessibility-issues" class="c-target-link">
  Issues with this site&rsquo;s accessibility can be submitted as a <a href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericwbailey.website/issues">Git&#8202;Hub issue</a>, or by <a data-message-subject="Accessibility issue" href="mailto:&#101;&#114;&#105;&#099;&#046;&#119;&#046;&#098;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#101;&#121;☛REMOVE-THIS☚&#064;&#103;&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;?subject=&#065;&#099;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#105;&#098;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#116;&#121;&#032;&#105;&#115;&#115;&#117;&#101;">emailing me directly</a>. I take these issues very seriously and will try to remedy the problem as quickly as time allows. A list of <a href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericwbailey.website/wiki/Accessibility-Testing-Warnings-and-Errors">known reported issues</a> is also available.
</p>
<p>
  Although I cannot guarantee that all content linked to, or embedded on this site is fully accessible, I try to choose sites and services that embrace <a href="https://inclusivedesignprinciples.info/">Inclusive Design principles</a>.
</p>
